title_full:
Henning Christiansen

              —
              OP.176 PENTHESILEA
            
              (Henning Christiansen Archive)
label: Henning Christiansen Archive
description:
Celebrated Danish Fluxus artist Henning Christiansen gets another deluxe (and lengthy) boxset, this time focusing on his most ambitious and highly-regarded project - music for Heinrich von Kleist's 24 scene tragedy "Penthesilea". RIYL Vladimir Ussachevsky, Robert Ashley, Akira Rabelais, Iannis Xennakis.

label: Late Music
description:
Sarah Davachi's most satisfying album yet is a love-letter to early music that expertly spans her interests in instrumentation, synthesis, minimalism and tradition. Rooted in the past, it's guided into the present by Davachi's unmistakably prudent hand - a patient examination of the through-line between choral, meditative drone and chamber music.
